reason": "Ứng viên đã chứng minh khả năng sử dụng một loạt các công cụ và ngôn ngữ lập trình quan trọng trong ngành Data Engineering, bao gồm Python, SQL, Docker, và Apache Airflow."}}', 'Tài liệu hồ sơ của ứng viên DO VAN CUONG cho thấy một nền tảng kỹ năng và kinh nghiệm phù hợp với vị trí Data Engineer. Tuy nhiên, ứng viên cần cải thiện khả năng tự đánh giá bản thân và xác định rõ ràng hơn mối liên kết giữa các yếu tố này.', 12, false, 'new', NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO public.cv_infos (id, cv_file_id, full_name, email, phone, date_of_birth, address, summary, educations, created_at, updated_at, "position", total_experience_years, raw_text, profile_data, quality_details, quality_reason, quality_score, is_marked, tag, note, work_type) VALUES (110, 157, 'Bao Long Pham', 'baolong.pham.ml@example.com', '+84 965 432 109', '2004-11-05', 'Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam', '', '[{"field": "Information Technology and Data Science", "degree": "Bachelor of Information Technology, Minor in Data Science", "university": "University of Science VNUHCM (HCMUS)", "graduation_year": "Expected Oct 2027"}]', '2026-06-24 23:07:20.000694', '2026-06-24 16:07:29.256234', 'Machine Learning Intern', 0, 'Bao Long Pham
Machine Learning Intern
DOB: 05/11/2004 | Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam
baolong.pham.ml@example.com | +84 965 432 109
linkedin.com/in/baolongphamml | github.com/baolongphamml
EDUCATION
University of Science VNUHCM (HCMUS)
Aug 2023 – Expected Oct 2027
Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam
Bachelor of Information Technology, Minor in Data Science
• Coursework: Data Structures, Algorithms, Databases, Computer Systems, Machine Learning, Data Mining, Data Visualization, Probability & Statistics, Natural Language Processing.
• GPA:
8.67/10 (as of May 2026)
PROJECTS
KKBox Customer Churn Prediction & AI Action Center
May 2026
Python, SQL, LightGBM, Power BI, Gemini API
• Engineered an end-to-end data pipeline on PostgreSQL, processing 30M+ raw transaction rows into a structured master_dataset via SQL-based RFM (Recency, Frequency, Monetary) feature engineering, reducing data volume by 97% before model training.
• Trained and benchmarked three classification models (LightGBM, XGBoost, Random Forest) on 825K users to predict churn; LightGBM achieved the best performance with AUC-ROC of 0.9517 and 80% recall on the churned class.
• Identified 61,922 high-risk users (churn probability >80%) representing 38M NTD in revenue at risk, by applying the trained model and segmenting outputs into four risk tiers for prioritized intervention.
• Integrated Google Gemini 2.5 Flash API to auto-generate personalized push notifications for each high-risk user profile, demonstrating a Prescriptive Analytics workflow bridging ML outputs and Marketing actions.
• Delivered a 3-page interactive Power BI dashboard (Churn Overview, Risk Model Analysis, AI Action Center) with synchronized slicers and DAX measures, enabling non-technical stakeholders to drill down from KPIs to individual user-level interventions.
Real-Time Pose Estimation & AI Push-Up Counter
March 2026
PyTorch, MMPose, Streamlit
• Deployed the RTMPose framework (CSPNeXt backbone, SimCC head) for real-time human pose estimation, achieving 1.9x faster inference (14.5 FPS) compared to HRNet baselines on consumergrade hardware.
• Conducted zero-shot evaluation on the Leeds Sports Pose (LSP) dataset, engineering an intersection mapping algorithm to resolve semantic mismatches between 17-point and 14-point skeletal formats.
• Developed a "Smart AI Push-Up Counter" web application, integrating a custom state machine for precise repetition tracking based on dynamic elbow joint angles.
• Implemented an anti-cheat posture validation system utilizing geometric vector analysis to monitor body alignment and provide real-time exercise feedback.
AIoT Elderly Fall Detection System
Jan 2026
Python, YOLO, ReactJS, Socket.IO
• Developed the frontend architecture using ReactJS for a real-time monitoring dashboard, integrating Socket.IO for instant alert popups with low latency.
• Conducted comprehensive Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) and evaluated YOLOv10n performance, analyzing the trade-offs between inference speed (3.4 ms) and detection recall.
• Collaborated in building an end-to-end pipeline that processes live camera feeds to detect abnormal postures, achieving an mAP@50 of 85.4% and a 93% recall rate.
TECHNICAL SKILLS
• Languages: Python, SQL (PostgreSQL, MongoDB), C/C++
• AI, ML & LLM: PyTorch, Scikit-learn, XGBoost, LightGBM, YOLO, RT-DETR, MMPose, Gemini API
• Data & BI: Pandas, NumPy, SQLAlchemy, ETL, Feature Engineering, Power BI, DAX, Scrapy
• Frameworks: FastAPI, Streamlit, Socket.IO
• Tools & Platforms: GitHub, Docker, Jupyter, VS Code, LATEX', '{"data": {"job_position": "Machine Learning Intern", "self_evaluation": "", "work_experience": [{"company": "", "duration": "Aug 2023 – Expected Oct 2027", "position": "Machine Learning Intern", "responsibility": "Engaged in real-time human pose estimation, developed a smart AI push-up counter web application, and built an end-to-end pipeline for elderly fall detection system. Achieved high performance metrics such as AUC-ROC of 0.9517 and mAP@50 of 85.4%."}], "basic_information": {"name": "Bao Long Pham", "email": "baolong.pham.ml@example.com", "phone": "+84 965 432 109", "status": "Completed", "address": "Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam", "date_of_birth": "2004-11-05"}, "education_background": [{"field": "Information Technology and Data Science", "degree": "Bachelor of Information Technology, Minor in Data Science", "university": "University of Science VNUHCM (HCMUS)", "graduation_year": "Expected Oct 2027"}], "skills_and_specialties": {"skills": ["Python", "SQL (PostgreSQL, MongoDB)", "C/C++", "PyTorch", "Scikit-learn", "XGBoost", "LightGBM", "YOLO", "RT-DETR", "MMPose", "Gemini API"], "certifications": []}, "total_experience_years": 0}, "cv_id": "278afc3c-014d-4faa-9f9d-889161969e82", "status": "success", "message": "CV đã được trích xuất cấu trúc thành công và lưu kho dưới dạng Semantic Chunking.", "raw_text": "Bao Long Pham\nMachine Learning Intern\nDOB: 05/11/2004 | Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam\nbaolong.pham.ml@example.com | +84 965 432 109\nlinkedin.com/in/baolongphamml | github.com/baolongphamml\nEDUCATION\nUniversity of Science VNUHCM (HCMUS)\nAug 2023 – Expected Oct 2027\nHo Chi Minh City, Vietnam\nBachelor of Information Technology, Minor in Data Science\n• Coursework: Data Structures, Algorithms, Databases, Computer Systems, Machine Learning, Data Mining, Data Visualization, Probability & Statistics, Natural Language Processing.\n• GPA:\n8.67/10 (as of May 2026)\nPROJECTS\nKKBox Customer Churn Prediction & AI Action Center\nMay 2026\nPython, SQL, LightGBM, Power BI, Gemini API\n• Engineered an end-to-end data pipeline on PostgreSQL, processing 30M+ raw transaction rows into a structured master_dataset via SQL-based RFM (Recency, Frequency, Monetary) feature engineering, reducing data volume by 97% before model training.\n• Trained and benchmarked three classification models (LightGBM, XGBoost, Random Forest) on 825K users to predict churn; LightGBM achieved the best performance with AUC-ROC of 0.9517 and 80% recall on the churned class.\n• Identified 61,922 high-risk users (churn probability >80%) representing 38M NTD in revenue at risk, by applying the trained model and segmenting outputs into four risk tiers for prioritized intervention.\n• Integrated Google Gemini 2.5 Flash API to auto-generate personalized push notifications for each high-risk user profile, demonstrating a Prescriptive Analytics workflow bridging ML outputs and Marketing actions.\n• Delivered a 3-page interactive Power BI dashboard (Churn Overview, Risk Model Analysis, AI Action Center) with synchronized slicers and DAX measures, enabling non-technical stakeholders to drill down from KPIs to individual user-level interventions.\nReal-Time Pose Estimation & AI Push-Up Counter\nMarch 2026\nPyTorch, MMPose, Streamlit\n• Deployed the RTMPose framework (CSPNeXt backbone, SimCC head) for real-time human pose estimation, achieving 1.9x faster inference (14.5 FPS) compared to HRNet baselines on consumergrade hardware.\n• Conducted zero-shot evaluation on the Leeds Sports Pose (LSP) dataset, engineering an intersection mapping algorithm to resolve semantic mismatches between 17-point and 14-point skeletal formats.\n• Developed a \"Smart AI Push-Up Counter\" web application, integrating a custom state machine for precise repetition tracking based on dynamic elbow joint angles.\n• Implemented an anti-cheat posture validation system utilizing geometric vector analysis to monitor body alignment and provide real-time exercise feedback.\nAIoT Elderly Fall Detection System\nJan 2026\nPython, YOLO, ReactJS, Socket.IO\n• Developed the frontend architecture using ReactJS for a real-time monitoring dashboard, integrating Socket.IO for instant alert popups with low latency.\n• Conducted comprehensive Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) and evaluated YOLOv10n performance, analyzing the trade-offs between inference speed (3.4 ms) and detection recall.\n• Collaborated in building an end-to-end pipeline that processes live camera feeds to detect abnormal postures, achieving an mAP@50 of 85.4% and a 93% recall rate.\nTECHNICAL SKILLS\n• Languages: Python, SQL (PostgreSQL, MongoDB), C/C++\n• AI, ML & LLM: PyTorch, Scikit-learn, XGBoost, LightGBM, YOLO, RT-DETR, MMPose, Gemini API\n• Data & BI: Pandas, NumPy, SQLAlchemy, ETL, Feature Engineering, Power BI, DAX, Scrapy\n• Frameworks: FastAPI, Streamlit, Socket.IO\n• Tools & Platforms: GitHub, Docker, Jupyter, VS Code, LATEX"}', '{"education": {"score": 1.5, "reason": "Học sinh tốt nghiệp cuối khóa từ một trường đại học/cao đẳng kỹ thuật/tài chính (ví dụ: Đại học Kinh tế TP.HCM, Đại học Công nghệ thông tin TP.HCM)."}, "self_evaluation": {"score": 0.0, "reason": "Không có đánh giá bản thân cụ thể hoặc liên quan đến sự phù hợp với văn hóa công ty."}, "work_experience": {"score": 2.0, "reason": "Đã làm việc trong vị trí实习生 (internship) trong một khoảng thời gian ngắn (1 năm hoặc ít hơn), và đã có những thành tựu đáng kể."}, "basic_information": {"score": 1.5, "reason": "Học sinh tốt nghiệp cuối khóa từ một trường đại học/cao đẳng kỹ thuật/tài chính (ví dụ: Đại học Kinh tế TP.HCM, Đại học Công nghệ thông tin TP.HCM)."}, "skills_specialties": {"score": 3.0, "reason": "Có kỹ năng Python, SQL, PyTorch, Scikit-learn, và các công cụ khác liên quan đến AI/ML, nhưng chưa đạt mức chuyên sâu như yêu cầu ở cấp độ 4.0 - 5.0 points."}}', 'Đánh giá tổng thể cho ứng viên này là 8 điểm. Họ có một nền tảng học vấn vững chắc từ một trường đại học kỹ thuật/tài chính, và đã có kinh nghiệm làm việc trong vị trí实习生 (internship) trong một khoảng thời gian ngắn. Tuy nhiên, họ chưa đạt mức chuyên sâu về AI/ML như yêu cầu ở cấp độ 4.0 - 5.0 points.', 8, false, 'new', NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO public.cv_infos (id, cv_file_id, full_name, email, phone, date_of_birth, address, summary, educations, created_at, updated_at, "position", total_experience_years, raw_text, profile_data, quality_details, quality_reason, quality_score, is_marked, tag, note, work_type) VALUES (112, 159, 'Dinh Quan Nguyen', 'dinhquan.data@example.com', '+84 945 678 123', '2003-08-20', 'Hanoi, Vietnam', 'Highly motivated IT graduate seeking a Data Engineer Intern position to apply and develop skills in building scalable data pipelines, data collection tooling, and analytical systems. Eager to contribute to data-driven projects in a large enterprise environment and grow into a senior data engineering role, with a long-term focus on real-time data processing and enterprise-scale data architecture.', '[{"field": "Information Technology", "degree": "Bachelor of Information Technology", "university": "University of Information Technology", "graduation_year": "2025"}]', '2026-06-24 23:08:03.260269', '2026-06-24 16:08:11.0711', 'Data Engineer Intern', 0, 'Dinh Quan Nguyen
Data Engineer Intern
DOB: 20/08/2003 | Hanoi, Vietnam
dinhquan.data@example.com | +84 945 678 123 linkedin.com/in/dinhquandata | github.com/dinhquandata
CAREER GOALS
Highly motivated IT graduate seeking a Data Engineer Intern position to apply and develop skills in building scalable data pipelines, data collection tooling, and analytical systems. Eager to contribute to data-driven projects in a large enterprise environment and grow into a senior data engineering role, with a long-term focus on real-time data processing and enterprise-scale data architecture.
EDUCATION
University of Information Technology
2021 – 2025
Bachelor of Information Technology GPA: 3.35/4.0
• Relevant coursework: Database Design & Development, Business Intelligence, Enterprise Web Software Development, Requirements Management, Website Design & Development.
PROJECTS
Retail Data Platform | Python, dbt Core, Apache Airflow, PostgreSQL, MinIO, Docker, Prophet 05/2026
Role: Full Stack Data Engineer
• Architected an end-to-end data platform for Vietnamese retail stores (electronics, home goods), ingesting data from KiotViet API (OAuth2, 15-min incremental polling) and Excel files into PostgreSQL via idempotent upsert with row_hash change detection.
• Built a 4-layer dbt transformation pipeline (raw → staging → intermediate → mart) with 11 models, 97 total tests (86 schema + 11 custom), achieving 97% test pass rate and enforcing referential integrity across all marts.
• Designed 6 analytical marts covering daily sales trends, RFM segmentation (12 customer segments), Customer 360 with churn probability, product performance ranking, inventory health (5 alert levels), and 90-day demand forecasting using Facebook Prophet with Vietnamese holiday calendars.
• Orchestrated 3 Airflow DAGs (daily ETL at 02:00, near-real-time KiotViet polling every 15 min, weekly Prophet forecast on Sundays) with retry/backoff, execution timeouts, and Zalo/email failure notifications.
• Containerised all 8 services (Airflow, dbt, PostgreSQL, MinIO, Metabase, pgAdmin) via Docker Compose, enabling one-command local deployment and straightforward cloud migration.
Lumiere AI Analytics tools | FastAPI, React, TypeScript, PostgreSQL, OpenAI API, Docker 08/2025 – 12/2025
Role:
Full Stack Developer
• Designed and implemented a full-stack data analytics platform enabling SMEs to query their data in natural language, auto-generate SQL, and receive AI-driven visualisations and insights.
End-to-End ELT Pipeline | Python, Apache Airflow, AWS S3/EC2/RDS, PostgreSQL, Docker, SQL 01/2026
Role: Full Stack Data Engineer
• Built a production-style ELT pipeline ingesting data from CSV and REST API sources into AWS S3 as a raw staging zone, then loading into PostgreSQL RDS for downstream analytics.
• Designed a Kimball-style star schema with 3 dimension tables ( dim.customer , dim.product , dim.date ) and 2 fact tables ( fact.orders , fact.daily_sales ), supporting time-series and segment-based reporting queries.
• Orchestrated the full workflow with an Apache Airflow DAG featuring incremental watermark processing, idempotent tasks, automatic retry policies, and XCom-based metadata passing between stages.
• Documented system architecture, data lineage, and built-in data quality checks (schema validation, referential integrity, duplicate prevention).
WORK EXPERIENCE
NTT DATA VDS Co., Ltd
02/2026 – 05/2026
AI Intern
• Designed and implemented an AI prototype that auto-generates and validates test cases from User Stories and SRS, targeting a 50% reduction in manual QA effort.
• Built a hybrid LLM architecture (local on-premise + OpenAI API), conducting trade-off analysis on accuracy, latency, and cost to balance data security and reasoning capability.
• Engineered prompt templates for functional, negative, and edge-case scenarios; enforced JSON/Gherkin output format for direct integration into automation pipelines.
• Implemented requirement-to-test traceability for automated coverage checks and early detection of missing or inconsistent scenarios.
• Delivered SRS, architecture design docs, and performance evaluation reports to international documentation standards.
Soi Bien Trung Thuc Joint Stock Company
01/2021 – 06/2021
Content Marketing
• Managed 3 social media pages and 2 groups (>3,000 members); ran multi-channel ad campaigns generating over 40M VND/day in revenue.
• Produced weekly/monthly ad spend reports and handled logistics, order closing, and inventory sourcing.
TECHNICAL SKILLS
• Data Engineering: Apache Airflow, dbt Core, ETL/ELT pipeline design, Star schema / Kimball modeling, Incremental loading, Data quality testing
• Databases: PostgreSQL, MySQL (SQL DDL/DML, Joins, Aggregation, Window functions); basic NoSQL awareness
• Programming: Python (pandas, NumPy, SQLAlchemy, requests, pytest), SQL
• Data Visualisation: Tableau, Metabase
CERTIFICATIONS & AWARDS
• Google Data Analytics Professional Certificate | Google 2024 • English Aptis B2 (168/200, equivalent IELTS 6.0) | British Council 2024 • "Promising Award" – Startup Competition in Agricultural Sector (AGRIUP 2025) 2025', '{"data": {"job_position": "Data Engineer Intern", "self_evaluation": "Highly motivated IT graduate seeking a Data Engineer Intern position to apply and develop skills in building scalable data pipelines, data collection tooling, and analytical systems. Eager to contribute to data-driven projects in a large enterprise environment and grow into a senior data engineering role, with a long-term focus on real-time data processing and enterprise-scale data architecture.", "work_experience": [{"company": "NTT DATA VDS Co., Ltd", "duration": "02/2026 - 05/2026", "position": "AI Intern", "responsibility": "Designed and implemented an AI prototype that auto-generates and validates test cases from User Stories and SRS, targeting a 50% reduction in manual QA effort. Built a hybrid LLM architecture (local on-premise + OpenAI API), conducted trade-off analysis on accuracy, latency, and cost to balance data security and reasoning capability. Engineered prompt templates for functional, negative, and edge-case scenarios; enforced JSON/Gherkin output format for direct integration into automation pipelines. Implemented requirement-to-test traceability for automated coverage checks."}], "basic_information": {"name": "Dinh Quan Nguyen", "email": "dinhquan.data@example.com", "phone": "+84 945 678 123", "status": "Completed", "address": "Hanoi, Vietnam", "date_of_birth": "2003-08-20"}, "education_background": [{"field": "Information Technology", "degree": "Bachelor of Information Technology", "university": "University of Information Technology", "graduation_year": "2025"}], "skills_and_specialties": {"skills": ["Python", "dbt Core", "Apache Airflow", "PostgreSQL", "MinIO", "Docker", "Prophet", "FastAPI", "React", "TypeScript", "AWS S3/EC2/RDS"], "certifications": []}, "total_experience_years": 0}, "cv_id": "99eea47c-e326-4500-bbfd-80e2c71d5d3f", "status": "success", "message": "CV đã được trích xuất cấu trúc thành công và lưu kho dưới dạng Semantic Chunking.", "raw_text": "Dinh Quan Nguyen\nData Engineer Intern\nDOB: 20/08/2003 | Hanoi, Vietnam\ndinhquan.data@example.com | +84 945 678 123 linkedin.com/in/dinhquandata | github.com/dinhquandata\nCAREER GOALS\nHighly motivated IT graduate seeking a Data Engineer Intern position to apply and develop skills in building scalable data pipelines, data collection tooling, and analytical systems. Eager to contribute to data-driven projects in a large enterprise environment and grow into a senior data engineering role, with a long-term focus on real-time data processing and enterprise-scale data architecture.\nEDUCATION\nUniversity of Information Technology\n2021 – 2025\nBachelor of Information Technology GPA: 3.35/4.0\n• Relevant coursework: Database Design & Development, Business Intelligence, Enterprise Web Software Development, Requirements Management, Website Design & Development.\nPROJECTS\nRetail Data Platform | Python, dbt Core, Apache Airflow, PostgreSQL, MinIO, Docker, Prophet 05/2026\nRole: Full Stack Data Engineer\n• Architected an end-to-end data platform for Vietnamese retail stores (electronics, home goods), ingesting data from KiotViet API (OAuth2, 15-min incremental polling) and Excel files into PostgreSQL via idempotent upsert with row_hash change detection.\n• Built a 4-layer dbt transformation pipeline (raw → staging → intermediate → mart) with 11 models, 97 total tests (86 schema + 11 custom), achieving 97% test pass rate and enforcing referential integrity across all marts.\n• Designed 6 analytical marts covering daily sales trends, RFM segmentation (12 customer segments), Customer 360 with churn probability, product performance ranking, inventory health (5 alert levels), and 90-day demand forecasting using Facebook Prophet with Vietnamese holiday calendars.\n• Orchestrated 3 Airflow DAGs (daily ETL at 02:00, near-real-time KiotViet polling every 15 min, weekly Prophet forecast on Sundays) with retry/backoff, execution timeouts, and Zalo/email failure notifications.\n• Containerised all 8 services (Airflow, dbt, PostgreSQL, MinIO, Metabase, pgAdmin) via Docker Compose, enabling one-command local deployment and straightforward cloud migration.\nLumiere AI Analytics tools | FastAPI, React, TypeScript, PostgreSQL, OpenAI API, Docker 08/2025 – 12/2025\nRole:\nFull Stack Developer\n• Designed and implemented a full-stack data analytics platform enabling SMEs to query their data in natural language, auto-generate SQL, and receive AI-driven visualisations and insights.\nEnd-to-End ELT Pipeline | Python, Apache Airflow, AWS S3/EC2/RDS, PostgreSQL, Docker, SQL 01/2026\nRole: Full Stack Data Engineer\n• Built a production-style ELT pipeline ingesting data from CSV and REST API sources into AWS S3 as a raw staging zone, then loading into PostgreSQL RDS for downstream analytics.\n• Designed a Kimball-style star schema with 3 dimension tables ( dim.customer , dim.product , dim.date ) and 2 fact tables ( fact.orders , fact.daily_sales ), supporting time-series and segment-based reporting queries.\n• Orchestrated the full workflow with an Apache Airflow DAG featuring incremental watermark processing, idempotent tasks, automatic retry policies, and XCom-based metadata passing between stages.\n• Documented system architecture, data lineage, and built-in data quality checks (schema validation, referential integrity, duplicate prevention).\nWORK EXPERIENCE\nNTT DATA VDS Co., Ltd\n02/2026 – 05/2026\nAI Intern\n• Designed and implemented an AI prototype that auto-generates and validates test cases from User Stories and SRS, targeting a 50% reduction in manual QA effort.\n• Built a hybrid LLM architecture (local on-premise + OpenAI API), conducting trade-off analysis on accuracy, latency, and cost to balance data security and reasoning capability.\n• Engineered prompt templates for functional, negative, and edge-case scenarios; enforced JSON/Gherkin output format for direct integration into automation pipelines.\n• Implemented requirement-to-test traceability for automated coverage checks and early detection of missing or inconsistent scenarios.\n• Delivered SRS, architecture design docs, and performance evaluation reports to international documentation standards.\nSoi Bien Trung Thuc Joint Stock Company\n01/2021 – 06/2021\nContent Marketing\n• Managed 3 social media pages and 2 groups (>3,000 members); ran multi-channel ad campaigns generating over 40M VND/day in revenue.\n• Produced weekly/monthly ad spend reports and handled logistics, order closing, and inventory sourcing.\nTECHNICAL SKILLS\n• Data Engineering: Apache Airflow, dbt Core, ETL/ELT pipeline design, Star schema / Kimball modeling, Incremental loading, Data quality testing\n• Databases: PostgreSQL, MySQL (SQL DDL/DML, Joins, Aggregation, Window functions); basic NoSQL awareness\n• Programming: Python (pandas, NumPy, SQLAlchemy, requests, pytest), SQL\n• Data Visualisation: Tableau, Metabase\nCERTIFICATIONS & AWARDS\n• Google Data Analytics Professional Certificate | Google 2024 • English Aptis B2 (168/200, equivalent IELTS 6.0) | British Council 2024 • \"Promising Award\" – Startup Competition in Agricultural Sector (AGRIUP 2025) 2025"}', '{"education": {"score": 1.5, "reason": "Học sinh tốt nghiệp cuối khóa từ một trường đại học/cao đẳng kỹ thuật (ví dụ: Đại học Kỹ thuật Hanoi, Đại học Kinh tế Quốc gia)"}, "self_evaluation": {"score": 0.5, "reason": "Giải thích tự đánh giá không rõ ràng về môi trường làm việc và mục tiêu nghề nghiệp"}, "work_experience": {"score": 0.0, "reason": "Ứng viên chỉ có kinh nghiệm làm việc trong khoảng thời gian ngắn và không liên quan đến công việc Data Engineer"}, "basic_information": {"score": 1.5, "reason": "Học sinh tốt nghiệp cuối khóa từ một trường đại học/cao đẳng kỹ thuật (ví dụ: Đại học Kỹ thuật Hanoi, Đại học Kinh tế Quốc gia)"}, "skills_specialties": {"score": 2.0, "reason": "Ứng viên biết Python, SQL cơ bản, sử dụng PostgreSQL, Apache Airflow, và các công cụ khác"}}', 'Tài liệu hồ sơ không cung cấp đủ thông tin để đánh giá kỹ năng chuyên môn và kinh nghiệm làm việc trong lĩnh vực Data Engineering. Điểm được chia đều cho yếu tố cơ bản, giáo dục và một phần nhỏ về tự đánh giá.', 8, false, 'new', NULL, NULL);
