– Present Majors: Information Technology | English: B1', '{"data": {"job_position": "Data Analyst Intern", "self_evaluation": "", "work_experience": [{"company": "[INFOCUS MEKONG RESEARCH]", "duration": "Mar 2026 – Present", "position": "DATA PROCESSING INTERN", "responsibility": "Identified and reported wording and logic errors across 3 survey projects; Processed 4 end-to-end survey datasets in SPSS within same-day turnaround covering variable renaming, labeling, and recoding delivering analysis-ready datasets to the analytics team; Independently developed SPSS syntax scripts for QC and insight validation, applied across 4 projects to standardize the data cleaning workflow."}], "basic_information": {"name": "Tien Dat Le", "email": "tiendat.data@example.com", "phone": "+84 978 123 456", "status": "Completed", "address": "Tra Vinh, Vietnam", "date_of_birth": "2004-11-04"}, "education_background": [{"field": "Information Technology", "degree": "BACHELOR OF INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY", "university": "Tra Vinh University", "graduation_year": "2022 – Present"}], "skills_and_specialties": {"skills": ["Data Analysis", "Data Processing", "Database"], "certifications": []}, "total_experience_years": 0}, "cv_id": "50b53488-3455-4901-9548-1b0690728fd9", "status": "success", "message": "CV đã được trích xuất cấu trúc thành công và lưu kho dưới dạng Semantic Chunking.", "raw_text": "Tien Dat Le\nData Analyst Intern\nDOB: 11/04/2004 | Tra Vinh, Vietnam tiendat.data@example.com | +84 978 123 456 linkedin.com/in/tiendat-data | github.com/tiendat-data\nSKILLS\n• Data Analysis: SQL, Python (Pandas, NumPy), Excel\n•\nSPSS, Data Cleaning, EDA\nData Processing:\n• Visualization: Power BI\n•\nSQL Server, MySQL, PostgreSQL\nDatabase:\nWORK EXPERIENCE\nDATA PROCESSING INTERN [INFOCUS MEKONG RESEARCH] Mar 2026 – Present\n• Identified and reported wording and logic errors across 3 survey projects by designing structured test cases for 4 question types (SA, MA, Grid, Ranking), preventing data quality issues before live deployment.\n• Processed 4 end-to-end survey datasets (500 records × 30–40 variables each) in SPSS within sameday turnaround covering variable renaming, labeling, and recoding delivering analysis-ready datasets to the analytics team.\n• Independently developed SPSS syntax scripts for QC and insight validation, applied across 4 projects to standardize the data cleaning workflow.\nPROJECTS\nCRM SALES PIPELINE ANALYSIS – Personal Project\nProject Link: View on GitHub\n• Identified ( ≈ 33%) Lead-to-Customer conversion rate, uncovering a major drop at Opportunity → Customer ( ≈ 20%), highlighting inefficiencies in late-stage closing and negotiation.\n• Discovered 70–80% loss rates in Agriculture & Mining → highlighted product-market misalignment .\n• Forecasted ( ≈ $244K) revenue (3-5 months) using open deals and historical win rate.\n• Segmented sales reps into high-efficiency vs. high-volume performers, enabling better performance evaluation.\nE-COMMERCE BOOK ANALYTICS (TIKI BOOK DATASET) – Personal Project Oct 2025 – Dec 2025\nProject Link: View on GitHub\n• Processed and cleaned 17,000+ records (products + reviews) using Python.\n• Conducted EDA → identified review count as key revenue driver and optimal discount level (=30%) for revenue maximization.\n• Built and compared ML models ( Linear Regression, Random Forest, XGBoost ) → selected Random Forest ( R 2 = 0 . 79 ).\n• Developed interactive Power BI dashboard for revenue insights and decision support.\nYOUTUBE TRENDING DATA WAREHOUSE (IN PROGRESS) – Personal Project March\n2026\nProject Link: View on GitHub\n• Built an end-to-end data pipeline using YouTube Data API v3 to collect 100,000+ trending videos and 1,000,000+ comments across multiple countries, with automatic rotation across 6 API keys to handle quota limits.\n• Designed a star schema Data Warehouse in PostgreSQL (5 dimensions, 2 fact tables) to support trend analysis across regions and categories.\n• Developing ML model to predict video trending probability.\nEDUCATION\nBACHELOR OF INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY – Tra Vinh University, In Progress 2022\n– Present Majors: Information Technology | English: B1"}', '{"education": {"score": 1.5, "reason": "Học vấn đạt chuẩn với BACHELOR OF INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY từ trường Tra Vinh University"}, "self_evaluation": {"score": 0.0, "reason": "Không có đánh giá cá nhân cụ thể hoặc rõ ràng"}, "work_experience": {"score": 2.0, "reason": "Có kinh nghiệm làm việc trong một môi trường công ty tư nhân (INFOCUS MEKONG RESEARCH) với vị trí DATA PROCESSING INTERN"}, "basic_information": {"score": 1.5, "reason": "Học vấn hiện tại là BACHELOR OF INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY từ trường Tra Vinh University"}, "skills_specialties": {"score": 0.0, "reason": "Không có kỹ năng hoặc chứng chỉ được liệt kê"}}', 'Tài liệu ứng viên chỉ cung cấp thông tin về học vấn và một số kinh nghiệm làm việc trong môi trường công ty tư nhân. Điểm đánh giá thấp nhất là do thiếu kỹ năng chuyên môn và đánh giá cá nhân rõ ràng.', 8, false, 'new', NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO public.cv_infos (id, cv_file_id, full_name, email, phone, date_of_birth, address, summary, educations, created_at, updated_at, "position", total_experience_years, raw_text, profile_data, quality_details, quality_reason, quality_score, is_marked, tag, note, work_type) VALUES (84, 127, 'Kevin Nguyen', 'kevin.nguyen.dev@example.com', '+84 987 654 321', '2004-10-15', 'Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam', 'Goal-oriented Fresher Java Developer with a strong foundation in Spring Boot and Microservices. Dedicated to building scalable backend systems and mastering clean code principles (SOLID). Proven ability to optimize database performance and implement secure authentication flows.', '[{"field": "Information Technology", "degree": "Bachelor of Information Technology", "university": "Saigon University", "graduation_year": "2026"}]', '2026-06-24 21:01:58.02724', '2026-06-24 14:02:07.120222', 'Fresher Java Backend Developer', 0, 'Kevin Nguyen
Fresher Java Backend Developer
DOB: 15/10/2004 | Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam
kevin.nguyen.dev@example.com | +84 987 654 321 linkedin.com/in/kevinnguyendev | github.com/kevinnguyendev
OBJECTIVE
Goal-oriented Fresher Java Developer with a strong foundation in Spring Boot and Microservices. Dedicated to building scalable backend systems and mastering clean code principles (SOLID). Proven ability to optimize database performance and implement secure authentication flows.
EDUCATION
Saigon University
2022 – 2026 (Expected)
Ho Chi Minh City
Bachelor of Information Technology GPA: 3.3/4.0
• Core Coursework: Data Structures & Algorithms, Object-Oriented Programming (Java), Database Management (MySQL), Web Development.
TECHNICAL SKILLS
• Languages: Java (Core), SQL, JavaScript, TypeScript, HTML/CSS
• Backend: Spring Boot, Spring MVC, Spring Data JPA, Spring Security, JWT, WebSocket, JUnit 5, Mockito
• Frontend: ReactJS, Redux Toolkit, Tailwind CSS, Bootstrap
• Tools & DevOps: Docker, Redis, Git, Maven, Postman, Swagger, SVN awareness
• Architecture: SOLID Principles, Design Patterns, Microservices Architecture
EXPERIENCE
TechNova Solutions
May 2025 – Dec 2025
Ho Chi Minh City
Backend Java Developer Intern
• Engineered backend features for e-commerce modules using Spring Boot , ensuring high data integrity for order management and payment flows.
• Enhanced system performance by optimizing complex SQL queries , reducing average API response times noticeably (measured 20% improvement in staging).
• Collaborated in an Agile/Scrum environment, contributing to daily stand-ups, code reviews, and sprint planning to ensure on-time delivery.
• Applied SOLID principles to refactor legacy code, improving maintainability and readability.
PROJECTS
Real-time Dating Application Spring Boot, WebSocket, MySQL, ReactJS, JWT Jan 2026 – April 2026
GitHub: github.com/kevinnguyendev/dating
• Built a real-time messaging engine using WebSocket & STOMP , achieving low-latency message delivery (tested under 50ms in local environment).
• Secured REST APIs with Spring Security & JWT , implementing role-based access control (RBAC) to protect user data endpoints.
• Optimized the matching feature by adding database indexes and refining JPA queries, noticeably improving response speed under typical load.
• Wrote unit and integration tests using JUnit 5 & Mockito, helping maintain reliable core logic and reducing regression bugs.
Secure E-commerce Platform Spring Boot, Redis, Docker, Cloudinary Aug 2025 – Dec 2025 GitHub: github.com/kevinnguyendev/ecommerce
• Added 2FA OTP authentication using Java Mail and Redis (TTL-based) to improve account security without complicating user experience.
• Integrated Redis caching for frequently accessed data, which visibly reduced database load and kept response times low during testing.
• Packaged the application with Docker to ensure consistent environments across development and staging.
• Used Cloudinary API to handle image resizing and lazy loading, improving frontend performance on slower networks.', '{"data": {"job_position": "Fresher Java Backend Developer", "self_evaluation": "Goal-oriented Fresher Java Developer with a strong foundation in Spring Boot and Microservices. Dedicated to building scalable backend systems and mastering clean code principles (SOLID). Proven ability to optimize database performance and implement secure authentication flows.", "work_experience": [{"company": "TechNova Solutions", "duration": "May 2025 – Dec 2025", "position": "Backend Java Developer Intern", "responsibility": "Engineered backend features for e-commerce modules using Spring Boot, ensuring high data integrity for order management and payment flows. Enhanced system performance by optimizing complex SQL queries, reducing average API response times noticeably (measured 20% improvement in staging). Collaborated in an Agile/Scrum environment, contributing to daily stand-ups, code reviews, and sprint planning to ensure on-time delivery. Applied SOLID principles to refactor legacy code, improving maintainability and readability."}, {"company": "TechNova Solutions", "duration": "Jan 2026 – April 2026", "position": "Real-time Dating Application Developer Intern", "responsibility": "Built a real-time messaging engine using WebSocket & STOMP, achieving low-latency message delivery (tested under 50ms in local environment). Secured REST APIs with Spring Security & JWT, implementing role-based access control (RBAC) to protect user data endpoints. Optimized the matching feature by adding database indexes and refining JPA queries, noticeably improving response speed under typical load. Wrote unit and integration tests using JUnit 5 & Mockito, helping maintain reliable core logic and reducing regression bugs."}, {"company": "TechNova Solutions", "duration": "Aug 2025 – Dec 2025", "position": "Secure E-commerce Platform Developer Intern", "responsibility": "Added 2FA OTP