ojects including a cross-platform pharmacy application and an IoT-integrated attendance system. Seeking a Backend & Mobile Developer Internship to contribute to application development, API design, and system integration while learning industrystandard engineering practices.\nEDUCATION\nUniversity of Washington\nB.S. Computer Engineering\nExpected Graduation: 2026\nSeattle, WA, USA\nPROJECTS\nMediGo (Cross-platform Pharmacy App)\n01/2026 – 06/2026\nFull-stack Developer\nFlutter, Dart, Python, Flask, MySQL, Docker, REST APIs\nStack:\ngithub.com/michaelchendev/medigo\nGitHub:\n• Developed MediGo, a comprehensive pharmacy application supporting Android, iOS, and Web platforms using a unified Flutter codebase.\n• Engineered a robust backend server using Python and Flask, integrating MySQL for reliable data storage and utilizing Docker to containerize the application for consistent deployment.\n• Designed and integrated RESTful APIs to ensure seamless data synchronization and consistent UI/UX experiences across all supported client platforms.\nIoT Attendance System\n09/2025 – 12/2025\nMobile App Developer\nFlutter, Dart, Provider, REST APIs\nStack:\ngithub.com/michaelchendev/iot-attendance\nGitHub:\n• Collaborated with a team to develop a cross-platform mobile application using Flutter and Dart for employees to monitor their daily attendance status and work history.\n• Integrated RESTful APIs from a Flask backend to handle user authentication (JWT) and retrieve real-time attendance logs.\n• Implemented data visualization features, including weekly statistical charts and monthly calendars, to track working hours intuitively.\n• Utilized Provider for efficient state management to handle user sessions, profile data synchronization, and UI updates.\nTetris Game on STM32\n02/2025 – 06/2025\nEmbedded Software Developer\nC/C++, STM32, FreeRTOS, Hardware RNG, PWM\nStack:\ngithub.com/michaelchendev/stm32-tetris\nGitHub:\n• Collaborated in a team of 3 to build a real-time Tetris game on the STM32F429I-DISCOVERY board; took ownership of the hardware logic and audio integration while coordinating with the team’s FreeRTOS and TouchGFX implementation.\n• Programmed the game’s tetromino generation logic by integrating the STM32’s Hardware Random Number Generator (RNG) to implement a fair, standard 7-piece \"bag\" system.\n• Configured hardware timers (TIM1) to generate precise PWM signals, driving a passive buzzer to play the Tetris theme music and responsive in-game sound effects.\nBlue Moon Apartment Fee Management 08/2024 – 12/2024 Java Developer Stack: Java, Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) GitHub: github.com/michaelchendev/apartment-management\n• Co-developed a comprehensive desktop application using Java within a team to efficiently manage apartment fees, including household data, utility costs, and parking charges.\n• Implemented data lookup features allowing administrators to track individual household fee records and generate aggregated monthly revenue statistics.\n• Designed and integrated role-based access control mechanisms to ensure data security and proper authorization for system operations.\nTECHNICAL SKILLS\n• Languages: Dart, Python, C/C++, Java, SQL\n• Databases: MySQL\n• Frameworks & Libraries: Flutter, Flask, Provider\n• Developer Tools: Git, Docker, STM32CubeIDE, VS Code, Cursor\n• Technologies & Concepts: RESTful APIs, JSON Web Tokens (JWT), Object-Oriented Programming (OOP), FreeRTOS, Hardware Timers/PWM"}', '{"education": {"score": 2.0, "reason": "Ứng viên đã hoàn thành chương trình cử nhân Công nghệ thông tin tại trường đại học University of Washington, một trường đại học uy tín ở Hoa Kỳ."}, "self_evaluation": {"score": 1.0, "reason": "Ứng viên đã cung cấp một bản tự đánh giá rõ ràng và liên quan đến vị trí ứng tuyển, nhưng chưa thể hiện sự kết nối cụ thể giữa các điểm mạnh của họ với lộ trình nghề nghiệp hoặc mục tiêu phát triển cá nhân."}, "work_experience": {"score": 3.5, "reason": "Ứng viên chỉ mô tả vị trí làm việc và trách nhiệm trong hồ sơ, nhưng không cung cấp thông tin về thời gian làm việc hoặc thành tích cụ thể. Tuy nhiên, với tư cách là một sinh viên cuối khóa, ứng viên có thể đang học hỏi các kỹ năng cần thiết cho vị trí."}, "basic_information": {"score": 1.5, "reason": "Giáo dục của ứng viên là B.S. Computer Engineering từ trường đại học University of Washington, được dự kiến tốt nghiệp vào năm 2026."}, "skills_specialties": {"score": 4.0, "reason": "Ứng viên đã cung cấp một danh sách kỹ năng và chứng chỉ liên quan đến Backend & Mobile Development, bao gồm Dart, Python, C/C++, Java, SQL, Flutter, Flask, Provider. Đây là những kỹ năng cần thiết cho vị trí ứng tuyển."}}', 'Ứng viên có nền tảng giáo dục vững chắc và kỹ năng phù hợp với vị trí Backend & Mobile Developer Intern. Tuy nhiên, bản tự đánh giá của họ chưa thể hiện sự kết nối rõ ràng giữa các điểm mạnh cá nhân và lộ trình nghề nghiệp cụ thể.', 12, false, 'new', NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO public.cv_infos (id, cv_file_id, full_name, email, phone, date_of_birth, address, summary, educations, created_at, updated_at, "position", total_experience_years, raw_text, profile_data, quality_details, quality_reason, quality_score, is_marked, tag, note, work_type) VALUES (59, 95, 'PHẠM NGỌC LAN THY', 'pnthangkth@gmail.com', '0372192004', NULL, 'Hà Nội, Vietnam', 'AI Engineer with hands-on experience building LLM, RAG, and multimodal retrieval systems for education and medical use cases. Built end-to-end AI products spanning ingestion, indexing, orchestration, and evidence-grounded generation across 7 content formats, with a focus on retrieval quality, hallucination reduction, and production-ready APIs.', '[{"field": "", "degree": "Computer Science", "university": "Posts and Telecommunications Institute of Technology (PTIT)", "graduation_year": "2026"}]', '2026-06-24 05:16:06.764038', '2026-06-26 10:06:27.700658', 'AI Engineer', 3, 'PHẠM NGỌC LAN THY
AI Engineer | LLM, RAG & Agentic Systems
Hà Nội, Vietnam | 0372192004 | pnthangkth@gmail.com | github.com/thangkh02
SUMMARY
AI Engineer with hands-on experience building LLM, RAG, and multimodal retrieval systems for education and medical use cases. Built end-to-end AI products spanning ingestion, indexing, orchestration, and evidence-grounded generation across 7 content formats, with a focus on retrieval quality, hallucination reduction, and production-ready APIs. Strong execution across Python, FastAPI, PyTorch, knowledge graphs, and agentic workflows.
EDUCATION
Posts and Telecommunications Institute of Technology (PTIT)
Computer Science
2022 – 2026
GPA: 3.23 / 4.00
PROJECTS
EduMentor Multi-Agent RAG Learning Platform
github.com/thangkh02/EduMentor
11/2025 – 12/2025
• Built an end-to-end multi-agent RAG platform that answered course questions across 7 content formats (PDF, TXT, DOC, slides, PPTX, images, video) by designing a unified ingestion, indexing, and retrieval pipeline.
• Implemented multimodal video Q&A that generated evidence-grounded answers from retrieved clips and transcripts by combining ASR, VLM-based understanding, and chunk-level retrieval.
• Developed an orchestration agent that improved response grounding by routing user intents, selecting tools, and synthesizing cited answers from retrieved context and external data sources.
• Reduced redundant recomputation for repeated queries by deploying GPTCache and retrieval-level caching for semantically similar requests.
• Shipped the platform as a web-ready backend within a 2-month development cycle using FastAPI, LangChain, PyTorch, MongoDB, and ChromaDB.
ViMed Medical Document RAG with Knowledge Graph Verification
github.com/thangkh02/VIMED-GRAPHRAG
12/2025 – 02/2026
• Built a medical GraphRAG system that improved evidence traceability by extracting knowledge triples with provenance and confidence metadata from document chunks.
• Designed a recursive tree index that enabled retrieval at multiple abstraction levels by clustering and summarizing documents into hierarchical representations.
• Engineered a hybrid retrieval pipeline that strengthened multi-hop reasoning by combining vector search with graph traversal to localize relevant subgraphs.
• Reduced unsupported responses by implementing a self-correcting verification loop that checked generated answers against citations and expanded retrieval when evidence was insufficient.
• Improved graph-based relevance modeling by training a Graph Neural Network for subgraph reranking and link prediction over the constructed knowledge graph.
• Delivered the system as a deployable API within a 3-month build cycle using FastAPI, PyTorch, ChromaDB, and Docker.
TECHNICAL SKILLS
Languages:
Python, Java, C/C++
Backend & APIs:
FastAPI, Flask, Django
ML / LLM:
PyTorch, Transformers, scikit-learn, TensorFlow/Keras, LangChain, LangGraph
RAG / AI Systems:
Vector Search, Knowledge Graph RAG, Multimodal RAG, PEFT (LoRA, QLoRA), Quantization, Distillation
Tools & Deployment:
Docker, MongoDB, ChromaDB, ONNX, llama.cpp, whisper.cpp, TFLite
CERTIFICATIONS
Samsung PTIT Applications of Algorithms (2024)
Samsung PTIT DevOps Fundamentals (2025)
