uments into hierarchical representations.\n• Engineered a hybrid retrieval pipeline that strengthened multi-hop reasoning by combining vector search with graph traversal to localize relevant subgraphs.\n• Reduced unsupported responses by implementing a self-correcting verification loop that checked generated answers against citations and expanded retrieval when evidence was insufficient.\n• Improved graph-based relevance modeling by training a Graph Neural Network for subgraph reranking and link prediction over the constructed knowledge graph.\n• Delivered the system as a deployable API within a 3-month build cycle using FastAPI, PyTorch, ChromaDB, and Docker.\nTECHNICAL SKILLS\nLanguages:\nPython, Java, C/C++\nBackend & APIs:\nFastAPI, Flask, Django\nML / LLM:\nPyTorch, Transformers, scikit-learn, TensorFlow/Keras, LangChain, LangGraph\nRAG / AI Systems:\nVector Search, Knowledge Graph RAG, Multimodal RAG, PEFT (LoRA, QLoRA), Quantization, Distillation\nTools & Deployment:\nDocker, MongoDB, ChromaDB, ONNX, llama.cpp, whisper.cpp, TFLite\nCERTIFICATIONS\nSamsung PTIT Applications of Algorithms (2024)\nSamsung PTIT DevOps Fundamentals (2025)\nBritish Council EnglishScore, B2 CEFR (2025)"}', '{"education": {"score": 2.0, "reason": "Ứng viên đã tốt nghiệp Computer Science tại PTIT (Posts and Telecommunications Institute of Technology), một trường đại học kỹ thuật hàng đầu ở Việt Nam."}, "self_evaluation": {"score": 1.0, "reason": "Ứng viên sử dụng các cụm từ chung như ''dynamic environment'' và ''hardworking individual'', nhưng không có liên kết cụ thể với công việc hoặc mục tiêu nghề nghiệp."}, "work_experience": {"score": 3.5, "reason": "Ứng viên có hai năm kinh nghiệm trong việc xây dựng hệ thống RAG và hệ thống GraphRAG cho các use case giáo dục và y tế. Đây là mức độ phù hợp với yêu cầu của một ứng viên AI Engineer."}, "basic_information": {"score": 1.5, "reason": "Họ và tên ứng viên được ghi rõ, địa chỉ và quốc gia cũng được xác định chính xác."}, "skills_specialties": {"score": 4.0, "reason": "Ứng viên có kỹ năng Python, FastAPI, PyTorch, knowledge graphs, và agentic workflows. Ngoài ra, họ cũng đã hoàn thành các chứng chỉ như ''Samsung PTIT Applications of Algorithms'' và ''Samsung PTIT DevOps Fundamentals''."}}', 'Ứng viên có nền tảng giáo dục vững chắc từ một trường đại học kỹ thuật hàng đầu, cùng với kinh nghiệm làm việc trong lĩnh vực AI và các chứng chỉ chuyên môn. Tuy nhiên, ứng viên cần cung cấp thêm thông tin cụ thể về khả năng của mình trong việc xây dựng hệ thống RAG và hệ thống GraphRAG để tăng điểm số.', 12, false, 'new', NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO public.cv_infos (id, cv_file_id, full_name, email, phone, date_of_birth, address, summary, educations, created_at, updated_at, "position", total_experience_years, raw_text, profile_data, quality_details, quality_reason, quality_score, is_marked, tag, note, work_type) VALUES (86, 133, 'Bao Long Pham', 'baolong.pham.ml@example.com', '+84 965 432 109', '2004-11-05', 'Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam', NULL, '[{"field": "Information Technology with a focus on Data Science", "degree": "Bachelor of Information Technology, Minor in Data Science", "university": "University of Science VNUHCM (HCMUS)", "graduation_year": "Expected Oct 2027"}]', '2026-06-24 21:45:03.235379', '2026-06-24 14:45:11.656916', 'Machine Learning Intern', 0, 'Bao Long Pham
Machine Learning Intern
DOB: 05/11/2004 | Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam
baolong.pham.ml@example.com | +84 965 432 109
linkedin.com/in/baolongphamml | github.com/baolongphamml
EDUCATION
University of Science VNUHCM (HCMUS)
Aug 2023 – Expected Oct 2027
Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam
Bachelor of Information Technology, Minor in Data Science
• Coursework: Data Structures, Algorithms, Databases, Computer Systems, Machine Learning, Data Mining, Data Visualization, Probability & Statistics, Natural Language Processing.
• GPA:
8.67/10 (as of May 2026)
PROJECTS
KKBox Customer Churn Prediction & AI Action Center
May 2026
Python, SQL, LightGBM, Power BI, Gemini API
• Engineered an end-to-end data pipeline on PostgreSQL, processing 30M+ raw transaction rows into a structured master_dataset via SQL-based RFM (Recency, Frequency, Monetary) feature engineering, reducing data volume by 97% before model training.
• Trained and benchmarked three classification models (LightGBM, XGBoost, Random Forest) on 825K users to predict churn; LightGBM achieved the best performance with AUC-ROC of 0.9517 and 80% recall on the churned class.
• Identified 61,922 high-risk users (churn probability >80%) representing 38M NTD in revenue at risk, by applying the trained model and segmenting outputs into four risk tiers for prioritized intervention.
• Integrated Google Gemini 2.5 Flash API to auto-generate personalized push notifications for each high-risk user profile, demonstrating a Prescriptive Analytics workflow bridging ML outputs and Marketing actions.
• Delivered a 3-page interactive Power BI dashboard (Churn Overview, Risk Model Analysis, AI Action Center) with synchronized slicers and DAX measures, enabling non-technical stakeholders to drill down from KPIs to individual user-level interventions.
Real-Time Pose Estimation & AI Push-Up Counter
March 2026
PyTorch, MMPose, Streamlit
• Deployed the RTMPose framework (CSPNeXt backbone, SimCC head) for real-time human pose estimation, achieving 1.9x faster inference (14.5 FPS) compared to HRNet baselines on consumergrade hardware.
• Conducted zero-shot evaluation on the Leeds Sports Pose (LSP) dataset, engineering an intersection mapping algorithm to resolve semantic mismatches between 17-point and 14-point skeletal formats.
• Developed a "Smart AI Push-Up Counter" web application, integrating a custom state machine for precise repetition tracking based on dynamic elbow joint angles.
• Implemented an anti-cheat posture validation system utilizing geometric vector analysis to monitor body alignment and provide real-time exercise feedback.
AIoT Elderly Fall Detection System
Jan 2026
Python, YOLO, ReactJS, Socket.IO
• Developed the frontend architecture using ReactJS for a real-time monitoring dashboard, integrating Socket.IO for instant alert popups with low latency.
• Conducted comprehensive Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) and evaluated YOLOv10n performance, analyzing the trade-offs between inference speed (3.4 ms) and detection recall.
• Collaborated in building an end-to-end pipeline that processes live camera feeds to detect abnormal postures, achieving an mAP@50 of 85.4% and a 93% recall rate.
TECHNICAL SKILLS
• Languages: Python, SQL (PostgreSQL, MongoDB), C/C++
• AI, ML & LLM: PyTorch, Scikit-learn, XGBoost, LightGBM, YOLO, RT-DETR, MMPose, Gemini API
• Data & BI: Pandas, NumPy, SQLAlchemy, ETL, Feature Engineering, Power BI, DAX, Scrapy
• Frameworks: FastAPI, Streamlit, Socket.IO
• Tools & Platforms: GitHub, Docker, Jupyter, VS Code, LATEX', '{"data": {"job_position": "Machine Learning Intern", "self_evaluation": null, "work_experience": [{"company": null, "duration": "Aug 2023 – Expected Oct 2027", "position": "Machine Learning Intern", "responsibility": "Engaged in multiple projects including Customer Churn Prediction & AI Action Center, Real-Time Pose Estimation & AI Push-Up Counter, and AIoT Elderly Fall Detection System. Responsibilities included data pipeline development, model training, feature engineering, real-time human pose estimation, and end-to-end pipeline construction."}], "basic_information": {"name": "Bao Long Pham", "email": "baolong.pham.ml@example.com", "phone": "+84 965 432 109", "status": "Completed", "address": "Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam", "date_of_birth": "2004-11-05"}, "education_background": [{"field": "Information Technology with a focus on Data Science", "degree": "Bachelor of Information Technology, Minor in Data Science", "university": "University of Science VNUHCM (HCMUS)", "graduation_year": "Expected Oct 2027"}], "skills_and_specialties": {"skills": ["Python", "SQL (PostgreSQL, MongoDB)", "C/C++", "PyTorch", "Scikit-learn", "XGBoost", "LightGBM", "YOLO", "RT-DETR", "MMPose", "Gemini API"], "certifications": []}, "total_experience_years": 0}, "cv_id": "0edbc959-1ef1-4364-9991-8ff60f2c1d6e", "status": "success", "message": "CV đã được trích xuất cấu trúc thành công và lưu kho dưới dạng Semantic Chunking.", "raw_text": "Bao Long Pham\nMachine Learning Intern\nDOB: 05/11/2004 | Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam\nbaolong.pham.ml@example.com | +84 965 432 109\nlinkedin.com/in/baolongphamml | github.com/baolongphamml\nEDUCATION\nUniversity of Science VNUHCM (HCMUS)\nAug 2023 – Expected Oct 2027\nHo Chi Minh City, Vietnam\nBachelor of Information Technology, Minor in Data Science\n• Coursework: Data Structures, Algorithms, Databases, Computer Systems, Machine Learning, Data Mining, Data Visualization, Probability & Statistics, Natural Language Processing.\n• GPA:\n8.67/10 (as of May 2026)\nPROJECTS\nKKBox Customer Churn Prediction & AI Action Center\nMay 2026\nPython, SQL, LightGBM, Power BI, Gemini API\n• Engineered an end-to-end data pipeline on PostgreSQL, processing 30M+ raw transaction rows into a structured master_dataset via SQL-based RFM (Recency, Frequency, Monetary) feature engineering, reducing data volume by 97% before model training.\n• Trained and benchmarked three classification models (LightGBM, XGBoost, Random Forest) on 825K users to predict churn; LightGBM achieved the best performance with AUC-ROC of 0.9517 and 80% recall on the churned class.\n• Identified 61,922 high-risk users (churn probability >80%) representing 38M NTD in revenue at risk, by applying the trained model and segmenting outputs into four risk tiers for prioritized intervention.\n• Integrated Google Gemini 2.5 Flash API to auto-generate personalized push notifications for each high-risk user profile, demonstrating a Prescriptive Analytics workflow bridging ML outputs and Marketing actions.\n• Delivered a 3-page interactive Power BI dashboard (Churn Overview, Risk Model Analysis, AI Action Center) with synchronized slicers and DAX measures, enabling non-technical stakeholders to drill down from KPIs to individual user-level interventions.\nReal-Time Pose Estimation & AI Push-Up Counter\nMarch 2026\nPyTorch, MMPose, Streamlit\n• Deployed the RTMPose framework (CSPNeXt backbone, SimCC head) for real-time human pose estimation, achieving 1.9x faster inference (14.5 FPS) compared to HRNet baselines on consumergrade hardware.\n• Conducted zero-shot evaluation on the Leeds Sports Pose (LSP) dataset, engineering an intersection mapping algorithm to resolve semantic mismatches between 17-point and 14-point skeletal formats.\n• Developed a \"Smart AI Push-Up Counter\" web application, integrating a custom state machine for precise repetition tracking based on dynamic elbow joint angles.\n• Implemented an ant