ophet, FastAPI, React, TypeScript, AWS S3/EC2/RDS"}}', 'Hồ sơ ứng viên chỉ có kinh nghiệm ngắn hạn và không liên quan đến vị trí Data Engineer Intern. Mặc dù ứng viên có một số kỹ năng phù hợp, nhưng chưa đủ để đạt mức điểm tối đa.', 12, false, 'new', NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO public.cv_infos (id, cv_file_id, full_name, email, phone, date_of_birth, address, summary, educations, created_at, updated_at, "position", total_experience_years, raw_text, profile_data, quality_details, quality_reason, quality_score, is_marked, tag, note, work_type) VALUES (28, 51, 'PHẠM NGỌC LAN THY', 'pnthangkth@gmail.com', '0372192004', NULL, 'Hà Nội, Vietnam', 'AI Engineer with hands-on experience building LLM, RAG, and multimodal retrieval systems for education and medical use cases. Built end-to-end AI products spanning ingestion, indexing, orchestration, and evidence-grounded generation across 7 content formats, with a focus on retrieval quality, hallucination reduction, and production-ready APIs. Strong execution across Python, FastAPI, PyTorch, knowledge graphs, and agentic workflows.', '[{"field": "", "degree": "Computer Science", "university": "Posts and Telecommunications Institute of Technology (PTIT)", "graduation_year": "2026"}]', '2026-06-19 14:42:48.881219', '2026-06-19 14:42:48.881219', 'AI Engineer', 3, 'PHẠM NGỌC LAN THY
AI Engineer | LLM, RAG & Agentic Systems
Hà Nội, Vietnam | 0372192004 | pnthangkth@gmail.com | github.com/thangkh02
SUMMARY
AI Engineer with hands-on experience building LLM, RAG, and multimodal retrieval systems for education and medical use cases. Built end-to-end AI products spanning ingestion, indexing, orchestration, and evidence-grounded generation across 7 content formats, with a focus on retrieval quality, hallucination reduction, and production-ready APIs. Strong execution across Python, FastAPI, PyTorch, knowledge graphs, and agentic workflows.
EDUCATION
Posts and Telecommunications Institute of Technology (PTIT)
Computer Science
2022 – 2026
GPA: 3.23 / 4.00
PROJECTS
EduMentor Multi-Agent RAG Learning Platform
github.com/thangkh02/EduMentor
11/2025 – 12/2025
• Built an end-to-end multi-agent RAG platform that answered course questions across 7 content formats (PDF, TXT, DOC, slides, PPTX, images, video) by designing a unified ingestion, indexing, and retrieval pipeline.
• Implemented multimodal video Q&A that generated evidence-grounded answers from retrieved clips and transcripts by combining ASR, VLM-based understanding, and chunk-level retrieval.
• Developed an orchestration agent that improved response grounding by routing user intents, selecting tools, and synthesizing cited answers from retrieved context and external data sources.
• Reduced redundant recomputation for repeated queries by deploying GPTCache and retrieval-level caching for semantically similar requests.
• Shipped the platform as a web-ready backend within a 2-month development cycle using FastAPI, LangChain, PyTorch, MongoDB, and ChromaDB.
ViMed Medical Document RAG with Knowledge Graph Verification
github.com/thangkh02/VIMED-GRAPHRAG
12/2025 – 02/2026
• Built a medical GraphRAG system that improved evidence traceability by extracting knowledge triples with provenance and confidence metadata from document chunks.
• Designed a recursive tree index that enabled retrieval at multiple abstraction levels by clustering and summarizing documents into hierarchical representations.
• Engineered a hybrid retrieval pipeline that strengthened multi-hop reasoning by combining vector search with graph traversal to localize relevant subgraphs.
• Reduced unsupported responses by implementing a self-correcting verification loop that checked generated answers against citations and expanded retrieval when evidence was insufficient.
• Improved graph-based relevance modeling by training a Graph Neural Network for subgraph reranking and link prediction over the constructed knowledge graph.
• Delivered the system as a deployable API within a 3-month build cycle using FastAPI, PyTorch, ChromaDB, and Docker.
TECHNICAL SKILLS
Languages:
Python, Java, C/C++
Backend & APIs:
FastAPI, Flask, Django
ML / LLM:
PyTorch, Transformers, scikit-learn, TensorFlow/Keras, LangChain, LangGraph
RAG / AI Systems:
Vector Search, Knowledge Graph RAG, Multimodal RAG, PEFT (LoRA, QLoRA), Quantization, Distillation
Tools & Deployment:
Docker, MongoDB, ChromaDB, ONNX, llama.cpp, whisper.cpp, TFLite
CERTIFICATIONS
Samsung PTIT Applications of Algorithms (2024)
Samsung PTIT DevOps Fundamentals (2025)
British Council EnglishScore, B2 CEFR (2025)', '{"data": {"job_position": "AI Engineer", "self_evaluation": "AI Engineer with hands-on experience building LLM, RAG, and multimodal retrieval systems for education and medical use cases. Built end-to-end AI products spanning ingestion, indexing, orchestration, and evidence-grounded generation across 7 content formats, with a focus on retrieval quality, hallucination reduction, and production-ready APIs. Strong execution across Python, FastAPI, PyTorch, knowledge graphs, and agentic workflows.", "work_experience": [{"company": "Posts and Telecommunications Institute of Technology (PTIT)", "duration": "2022 – 2026", "position": "Computer Science", "responsibility": "Built an end-to-end multi-agent RAG platform that answered course questions across 7 content formats, implemented multimodal video Q&A, developed an orchestration agent for improved response grounding, reduced redundant recomputation with GPTCache and retrieval-level caching, and delivered the platform as a web-ready backend using FastAPI, LangChain, PyTorch, MongoDB, and ChromaDB. Built a medical GraphRAG system that improved evidence traceability by extracting knowledge triples from document chunks, designed a recursive tree index for retrieval at multiple abstraction levels, engineered a hybrid retrieval pipeline combining vector search with graph traversal to localize relevant subgraphs, reduced unsupported responses by implementing a self-correcting verification loop, and delivered the system as a deployable API using FastAPI, PyTorch, ChromaDB, and Docker."}], "basic_information": {"name": "PHẠM NGỌC LAN THY", "email": "pnthangkth@gmail.com", "phone": "0372192004", "status": "Completed", "address": "Hà Nội, Vietnam", "date_of_birth": ""}, "education_background": [{"field": "", "degree": "Computer Science", "university": "Posts and Telecommunications Institute of Technology (PTIT)", "graduation_year": "2026"}], "skills_and_specialties": {"skills": ["Python", "Java", "C/C++", "FastAPI", "Flask", "Django", "PyTorch", "transformers", "scikit-learn", "TensorFlow/Keras", "LangChain", "LangGraph", "Vector Search", "Knowledge Graph RAG", "Multimodal RAG", "PEFT (LoRA, QLoRA)", "Quantization", "Distillation", "Docker", "MongoDB", "ChromaDB", "ONNX", "llama.cpp", "whisper.cpp", "TFLite"], "certifications": ["Samsung PTIT Applications of Algorithms (2024)", "Samsung PTIT DevOps Fundamentals (2025)", "British Council EnglishScore, B2 CEFR (2025)"]}, "total_experience_years": 3}, "cv_id": "98e769a1-2f30-4429-a574-350b30cff8cf", "status": "success", "message": "CV đã được trích xuất cấu trúc thành công và lưu kho dưới dạng Semantic Chunking.", "raw_text": "PHẠM NGỌC LAN THY\nAI Engineer | LLM, RAG & Agentic Systems\nHà Nội, Vietnam | 0372192004 | pnthangkth@gmail.com | github.com/thangkh02\nSUMMARY\nAI Engineer with hands-on experience building LLM, RAG, and multimodal retrieval systems for education and medical use cases. Built end-to-end AI products spanning ingestion, indexing, orchestration, and evidence-grounded generation across 7 content formats, with a focus on retrieval quality, hallucination reduction, and production-ready APIs. Strong execution across Python, FastAPI, PyTorch, knowledge graphs, and agentic workflows.\nEDUCATION\nPosts and Telecommunications Institute of Technology (PTIT)\nComputer Science\n2022 – 2026\nGPA: 3.23 / 4.00\nPROJECTS\nEduMentor Multi-Agent RAG Learning Platform\ngithub.com/thangkh02/EduMentor\n11/2025 – 12/2025\n• Built an end-to-end multi-agent RAG platform that answered course questions across 7 content formats (PDF, TXT, DOC, slides, PPTX, images, video) by designing a unified ingestion, indexing, and retrieval pipeline.\n• Implemented multimodal video Q&A that generated evidence-grounded answers from retrieved clips and transcripts by combining ASR, VLM-based understanding, and chunk-level retrieval.\n• Developed an orchestration agent that improved response grounding by routing user intents, selecting tools, and synthesizing cited answers from retrieved context and external data sources.\n• Reduced redundant recomputation for repeated queries by deploying GPTCache and retrieval-level caching for semantically similar requests.\n• Shipped the platform as a web-ready backend within a 2-month development cycle using FastAPI, LangChain, PyTorch, MongoDB, and ChromaDB.\nViMed Medical Document RAG with Knowledge Graph Verification\ngithub.com/thangkh02/VIMED-GRAPHRAG\n12/2025 – 02/2026\n• Built a medical GraphRAG system that improved evidence traceability by extracting knowledge triples with provenance and confidence metadata from document chunks.\n• Designed a recursive tree index that enabled retrieval at multiple abstraction levels by clustering and summarizing documents into hierarchical representations.\n• Engineered a hybrid retrieval pipeline that strengthened multi-hop reasoning by combining vector search with graph traversal to localize relevant subgraphs.\n• Reduced unsupported responses by implementing a self-correcting verification loop that checked generated answers against citations and expanded retrieval when evidence was insufficient.\n• Improved graph-based relevance modeling by training a Graph Neural Network for subgraph reranking and link prediction over the constructed knowledge graph.\n• Delivered the system as a deployable API within a 3-month build cycle using FastAPI, PyTorch, ChromaDB, and Docker.\nTECHNICAL SKILLS\nLanguages:\nPython, Java, C/C++\nBackend & APIs:\nFastAPI, Flask, Django\nML / LLM:\nPyTorch, Transformers, scikit-learn, TensorFlow/Keras, LangChain, LangGraph\nRAG / AI Systems:\nVector Search, Knowledge Graph RAG, Multimodal RAG, PEFT (LoRA, QLoRA), Quantization, Distillation\nTools & Deployment:\nDocker, MongoDB, ChromaDB, ONNX, llama.cpp, whisper.cpp, TFLite\nCERTIFICATIONS\nSamsung PTIT Applications of Algorithms (2024)\nSamsung PTIT DevOps Fundamentals (2025)\nBritish Council EnglishScore, B2 CEFR (2025)"}', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, 'new', NULL, NULL);
