DOB: 22/09/2004 | Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam
minhphat.risk@example.com | +84 901 234 567
linkedin.com/in/minhphat-risk | github.com/minhphat-risk
OBJECTIVE
Applied Mathematics student with strong SQL, Python, and statistical modeling skills, seeking to support MoMo’s Credit Risk Management team in portfolio analytics, risk monitoring, underwriting analytics, and automated reporting.
EDUCATION
University of Economics and Law (VNU-HCM)
Bachelor of Applied Mathematics in Economics, Management, and Finance
Vietnam Sep 2023 - Present Ho Chi Minh City,
• Current GPA: 8.30 / 10.0 (Coursework Completed: Aug 2026 | Expected Graduation Decision: Feb 2027)
• Relevant Coursework: Econometrics, Panel Data Analysis, Financial Time Series Analysis, Statistical Programming, Introduction to Machine Learning, Data Mining, Databases, Operations Research.
HONORS & AWARDS
BUSINESS CASES & ACADEMIC PROJECTS
E-Banking Security & Hyper-Personalization System | G’CONTEST 2026
2026
• Modeled a Star Schema database (290K users, 16M+ logs) and performed data quality checks to ensure reliable downstream modeling.
• Engineered an anomaly-monitoring framework using Isolation Forest and business rules, isolating 93 critical risk cases and improving review efficiency for safe users.
• Trained an XGBoost credit propensity pipeline; improved interpretability using SHAP values to help risk officers deploy transparent underwriting policies.
• Segmented users into 4 behavioral personas using the Hungarian Algorithm , enabling targeted in-app campaigns and more precise customer segmentation .
ITB Omnichannel Restructuring Strategy | Business Intelligence Season 9
2025
• Executed portfolio monitoring on 2M+ records using SQL (CTEs, Window Functions) to identify root causes behind an 85% customer churn rate.
• Designed a channel restructuring plan to decommission unprofitable storefronts, automating customer transition to high-margin digital channels.
• Constructed automated Power BI dashboards and financial forecasts for stakeholder reporting , projecting an 11.3% net profit expansion.
|
2025
• Built a credit-scoring pipeline on 50,000 records, evaluating Tree-based models to improve delin-
quency prediction and isolate top drivers of default.
• Segmented unbanked demographics into 4 risk profiles using K-Means Clustering, enabling policy
design for an alternative-data micro-lending framework.
TECHNICAL SKILLS
• SQL Analytics & Databases: SQL (MySQL), Window Functions, CTEs, Joins, Aggregation, Data Quality Checks
