2023 – Present
Ha Noi, Vietnam
PROJECTS
Chotot Used Car Data Pipeline
April 2026
/external-link-alt
Python, PySpark, Delta Lake, PostgreSQL, Airflow, Metabase
• Built an end-to-end used car data pipeline to scrape Chotot listings using Python, BeautifulSoup, Requests, and Pandas.
• Stored raw historical snapshots in a Bronze layer and processed cleaned data with PySpark using a medallion architecture.
• Implemented CDC-style upsert logic with Delta Lake to track changes in listing prices, availability, and vehicle information.
• Orchestrated ETL workflows with Apache Airflow, loaded curated Gold-layer data into PostgreSQL, and built Metabase dashboards for market insights.
Banking Lakehouse Pipeline
May 2026 /external-link-alt
PostgreSQL, Debezium, Kafka, MinIO, Snowflake, dbt, Airflow, Power BI
• Built an end-to-end banking data pipeline using PostgreSQL, Debezium, Kafka, and MinIO to capture CDC events from source tables.
• Consumed Kafka events and stored raw banking data as Parquet files in MinIO to simulate a data lake storage layer.
• Loaded raw data into Snowflake and transformed it with dbt into staging models, fact tables, dimension tables, and SCD Type 2 snapshots.
• Orchestrated data loading and transformation workflows with Apache Airflow and visualized banking metrics in Power BI.
LANGUAGES
English: Reading comprehension, able to read technical documentation', '{"data": {"job_position": "Data Engineer Intern", "self_evaluation": "Final-year Computer Science student seeking a Data Engineer Intern opportunity. Hands-on experience in building data pipelines and working with large-scale datasets through academic and personal projects. Strong interest in data engineering and scalable data systems, with a desire to apply technical skills in a real-world environment.", "work_experience": [{"company": "VNPT AI", "duration": "2023 – Present", "position": "Project Support Collaborator", "responsibility": "Labeled and reviewed training data for AI-related projects, ensuring data accuracy and consistency. Created test cases and performed application testing to check features and report issues."}], "basic_information": {"name": "Do Xuan Khanh", "email": "doxuankhanh674@gmail.com", "phone": "+84 886 653 746", "status": "Completed", "address": "Mo Lao, Ha Dong, Ha Noi, Vietnam", "date_of_birth": ""}, "education_background": [{"field": "", "degree": "Computer Science", "university": "Posts and Telecommunications Institute of Technology (PTIT)", "graduation_year": "2022 – Present"}], "skills_and_specialties": {"skills": ["Python", "Java", "SQL", "Apache Spark", "Kafka", "Airflow", "Snowflake", "dbt", "ETL/ELT Pipelines", "Web Scraping", "CDC"], "certifications": []}, "total_experience_years": 0}, "cv_id": "4061bfd5-2fd0-43f1-8287-7cb4d4fc2ad2", "status": "success", "message": "CV đã được trích xuất cấu trúc thành công và lưu kho dưới dạng Semantic Chunking.", "raw_text": "Mo Lao, Ha Dong, Ha Noi\nDo Xuan Khanh\n/envelope\ndoxuankhanh674@gmail.com\n/github\n+84 886 653 746\nOBJECTIVE\nFinal-year Computer Science student seeking a Data Engineer Intern opportunity. Hands-on experience in building data pipelines and working with large-scale datasets through academic and personal projects. Strong interest in data engineering and scalable data systems, with a desire to apply technical skills in a real-world environment.\nEDUCATION\nPosts and Telecommunications Institute of Technology (PTIT) Computer Science\n2022 – Present\nHa Noi, Vietnam\n• Focused on data systems, programming, databases, and applied machine learning.\n• Relevant foundation: Data Structures and Algorithms, Object-Oriented Programming, Database Systems, System Analysis and Design.\nSKILLS\nProgramming Languages:\nPython, Java, SQL\nDatabases:\nSQL Server, PostgreSQL\nData Visualization:\nPower BI, Excel\nData Engineering:\nApache Spark, Kafka, Airflow, Snowflake, dbt\nData Acquisition & ETL:\nETL/ELT Pipelines, Web Scraping, CDC\nDeveloper Tools:\nGit, GitHub, Docker, Linux\nEXPERIENCE\nProject Support Collaborator\nVNPT AI\n• Labeled and reviewed training data for AI-related projects, ensuring data accuracy and consistency.\n• Created test cases and performed application testing to check features and report issues.\n2023 – Present\nHa Noi, Vietnam\nPROJECTS\nChotot Used Car Data Pipeline\nApril 2026\n/external-link-alt\nPython, PySpark, Delta Lake, PostgreSQL, Airflow, Metabase\n• Built an end-to-end used car data pipeline to scrape Chotot listings using Python, BeautifulSoup, Requests, and Pandas.\n• Stored raw historical snapshots in a Bronze layer and processed cleaned data with PySpark using a medallion architecture.\n• Implemented CDC-style upsert logic with Delta Lake to track changes in listing prices, availability, and vehicle information.\n• Orchestrated ETL workflows with Apache Airflow, loaded curated Gold-layer data into PostgreSQL, and built Metabase dashboards for market insights.\nBanking Lakehouse Pipeline\nMay 2026 /external-link-alt\nPostgreSQL, Debezium, Kafka, MinIO, Snowflake, dbt, Airflow, Power BI\n• Built an end-to-end banking data pipeline using PostgreSQL, Debezium, Kafka, and MinIO to capture CDC events from source tables.\n• Consumed Kafka events and stored raw banking data as Parquet files in MinIO to simulate a data lake storage layer.\n• Loaded raw data into Snowflake and transformed it with dbt into staging models, fact tables, dimension tables, and SCD Type 2 snapshots.\n• Orchestrated data loading and transformation workflows with Apache Airflow and visualized banking metrics in Power BI.\nLANGUAGES\nEnglish: Reading comprehension, able to read technical documentation"}', '{"education": {"score": 2.0, "reason": "Giáo dục tại Posts and Telecommunications Institute of Technology (PTIT) với chuyên ngành Computer Science"}, "self_evaluation": {"score": 1.0, "reason": "Ứng viên chỉ rõ sự quan tâm đến Data Engineering và hệ thống dữ liệu lớn, nhưng chưa thể hiện rõ ràng mối liên kết giữa những điểm mạnh của mình và lộ trình nghề nghiệp cụ thể"}, "work_experience": {"score": 3.5, "reason": "Ứng viên có kinh nghiệm làm việc trong một công ty lớn (VNPT AI), đặc biệt là trong việc xây dựng và quản lý các pipeline dữ liệu"}, "basic_information": {"score": 1.5, "reason": "Giáo dục tại Posts and Telecommunications Institute of Technology (PTIT) với chuyên ngành Computer Science"}, "skills_specialties": {"score": 4.0, "reason": "Ứng viên nắm vững nhiều kỹ năng và công cụ cần thiết cho vị trí Data Engineer, bao gồm Python, Apache Spark, Kafka, Airflow, Snowflake"}}', 'Ứng viên có nền tảng giáo dục tốt về chuyên ngành Computer Science từ PTIT, và đã có kinh nghiệm làm việc trong một công ty lớn với vị trí Project Support Collaborator. Tuy nhiên, ứng viên chưa thể hiện rõ ràng mối liên kết giữa những điểm mạnh của mình và lộ trình nghề nghiệp cụ thể.', 12, false, 'new', NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO public.cv_infos (id, cv_file_id, full_name, email, phone, date_of_birth, address, summary, educations, created_at, updated_at, "position", total_experience_years, raw_text, profile_data, quality_details, quality_reason, quality_score, is_marked, tag, note, work_type) VALUES (38, 67, 'PHẠM NGỌC LAN THY', 'pnthangkth@gmail.com', '0372192004', NULL, 'Hà Nội, Vietnam', 'AI Engineer with hands-on experience building LLM, RAG, and multimodal retrieval systems for education and medical use cases. Built end-to-end AI products spanning ingestion, indexing, orchestration, and evidence-grounded generation across 7 content formats, with a focus on retrieval quality, hallucination reduction, and production-ready APIs. Strong execution across Python, FastAPI, PyTorch, knowledge graphs, and agentic workflows.', '[{"field": "", "degree": "Computer Science", "university": "Posts and Telecommunications Institute of Technology (PTIT)", "graduation_year": "2026"}]', '2026-06-19 22:19:43.194307', '2026-06-19 15:19:55.012769', 'AI Engineer', 3, 'PHẠM NGỌC LAN THY
AI Engineer | LLM, RAG & Agentic Systems
Hà Nội, Vietnam | 0372192004 | pnthangkth@gmail.com | github.com/thangkh02
SUMMARY
AI Engineer with hands-on experience building LLM, RAG, and multimodal retrieval systems for education and medical use cases. Built end-to-end AI products spanning ingestion, indexing, orchestration, and evidence-grounded generation across 7 content formats, with a focus on retrieval quality, hallucination reduction, and production-ready APIs. Strong execution across Python, FastAPI, PyTorch, knowledge graphs, and agentic workflows.
EDUCATION
Posts and Telecommunications Institute of Technology (PTIT)
Computer Science
2022 – 2026
GPA: 3.23 / 4.00
PROJECTS
EduMentor Multi-Agent RAG Learning Platform
github.com/thangkh02/EduMentor
11/2025 – 12/2025
• Built an end-to-end multi-agent RAG platform that answered course questions across 7 content formats (PDF, TXT, DOC, slides, PPTX, images, video) by designing a unified ingestion, indexing, and retrieval pipeline.
• Implemented multimodal video Q&A that generated evidence-grounded answers from retrieved clips and transcripts by combining ASR, VLM-based understanding, and chunk-level retrieval.
• Developed an orchestration agent that improved response grounding by routing user intents, selecting tools, and synthesizing cited answers from retrieved context and external data sources.
• Reduced redundant recomputation for repeated queries by deploying GPTCache and retrieval-level caching for semantically similar requests.
• Shipped the platform as a web-ready backend within a 2-month development cycle using FastAPI, LangChain, PyTorch, MongoDB, and ChromaDB.
ViMed Medical Document RAG with Knowledge Graph Verification
github.com/thangkh02/VIMED-GRAPHRAG
12/2025 – 02/2026
• Built a medical GraphRAG system that improved evidence traceability by extracting knowledge triples with provenance and confidence metadata from document chunks.
• Designed a recursive tree index that enabled retrieval at multiple abstraction levels by clustering and summarizing documents into hierarchical representations.
• Engineered a hybrid retrieval pipeline that strengthened multi-hop reasoning by combining vector search with graph traversal to localize relevant subgraphs.
• Reduced unsupported responses by implementing a self-correcting verification loop that checked generated answers against citations and expanded retrieval when evidence was insufficient.
• Improved graph-based relevance modeling by training a Graph Neural Network for subgraph reranking and link prediction over the constructed knowledge graph.
• Delivered the system as a deployable API within a 3-month build cycle using FastAPI, PyTorch, ChromaDB, and Docker.
TECHNICAL SKILLS
Languages:
Python, Java, C/C++
Backend & APIs:
FastAPI, Flask, Django
ML / LLM:
PyTorch, Transformers, scikit-learn, TensorFlow/Keras, LangChain, LangGraph
RAG / AI Systems:
Vector Search, Knowledge Graph RAG, Multimodal RAG, PEFT (LoRA, QLoRA), Quantization, Distillation
Tools & Deployment:
Docker, MongoDB, ChromaDB, ONNX, llama.cpp, whisper.cpp, TFLite
CERTIFICATIONS
Samsung PTIT Applications of Algorithms (2024)
Samsung PTIT DevOps Fundamentals (2025)
