Social Sphere | Full Stack Developer GitHub: github.com/lehaidangdev/social-sphere-app
07/2025 – 02/2026
• Project Description: A large-scale social network web application built to handle multiple user interactions and real-time features.
• Main Functions:
– Developed a real-time notification system with online/offline status tracking using Socket.IO.
– Implemented robust authentication & authorization using JWT, Session, and Cookie (similar to Google auth flow).
– Built core features including post management (like, comment, share) and group management (member approval, sorting posts).
– Designed a user management module (profile editing, friend suggestions, relationship management) and a feed algorithm based on user preferences.
– Optimized performance through cursor/offset pagination, server-side folder image storage to reduce database load, and data caching.
• Technologies: TypeScript, Express.js, Sequelize ORM, SQL Server, Jest, HTML/CSS/JS, REST API, MVC.
Retail Analytics Dashboard | Backend Developer
12/2025 – 01/2026
github.com/lehaidangdev/retail-analytics-api
GitHub:
• Project Description: A comprehensive dashboard system designed for monitoring sales orders, managing customers, and generating revenue statistics.
• Main Functions: Built endpoints for real-time monitoring and near real-time analytics, dynamic revenue reporting, and detailed customer/order statistics aggregations.
• Technologies: ASP.NET Core, SQL Server, Ocelot API Gateway, REST API.', '{"data": {"job_position": "Intern Backend Developer", "self_evaluation": "Backend-focused Full Stack Developer with strong experience in building scalable RESTful APIs using TypeScript (Express.js) and ASP.NET Core. Experienced in designing real-time systems, authentication mechanisms, and database optimization. Passionate about clean architecture, performance optimization, and writing maintainable code.", "work_experience": [{"company": "", "duration": "07/2025 – 02/2026", "position": "Full Stack Developer", "responsibility": "Developed a real-time notification system with online/offline status tracking using Socket.IO. Implemented robust authentication & authorization using JWT, Session, and Cookie (similar to Google auth flow). Built core features including post management (like, comment, share) and group management (member approval, sorting posts). Designed a user management module (profile editing, friend suggestions, relationship management) and a feed algorithm based on user preferences. Optimized performance through cursor/offset pagination, server-side folder image storage to reduce database load, and data caching."}, {"company": "", "duration": "12/2025 – 01/2026", "position": "Backend Developer", "responsibility": "Built endpoints for real-time monitoring and near real-time analytics. Dynamic revenue reporting, and detailed customer/order statistics aggregations."}], "basic_information": {"name": "Le Hai Dang", "email": "lehaidang.dev@example.com", "phone": "+84 912 345 678", "status": "Completed", "address": "Hanoi, Vietnam", "date_of_birth": "2005-09-24"}, "education_background": [{"field": "", "degree": "Software Engineering", "university": "Hanoi University of Industry", "graduation_year": ""}], "skills_and_specialties": {"skills": ["TypeScript/JavaScript", "C#", "HTML/CSS", "Jest"], "certifications": []}, "total_experience_years": 0}, "cv_id": "259e20cd-d53a-4d45-9f2e-e57d19efebed", "status": "success", "message": "CV đã được trích xuất cấu trúc thành công và lưu kho dưới dạng Semantic Chunking.", "raw_text": "Le Hai Dang\nIntern Backend Developer\nDOB: 24/09/2005 | Hanoi, Vietnam\nlehaidang.dev@example.com | +84 912 345 678 linkedin.com/in/lehaidangdev | github.com/lehaidangdev\nPERSONAL SUMMARY\nBackend-focused Full Stack Developer with strong experience in building scalable RESTful APIs using TypeScript (Express.js) and ASP.NET Core. Experienced in designing real-time systems, authentication mechanisms, and database optimization. Passionate about clean architecture, performance optimization, and writing maintainable code.\nEDUCATION\nHanoi University of Industry\nMajor: Software Engineering\n• Achievement: Academic Excellence Scholarship Semester 2, 2024.\n2023 – 2027 (Expected) Hanoi, Vietnam\nSKILLS\n• Programming Languages:\nTypeScript/JavaScript, C#, HTML/CSS, Jest\n• Tools: Visual Studio Code, Visual Studio, Git/GitHub, Postman, Cursor AI, Docker\n• Databases: SQL Server, MongoDB, Redis\n• Frameworks & Tech: Express.js, Sequelize, ASP.NET Core, RESTful API, MVC, Microservices, Dependency Injection (DI), Socket.IO, JWT, Multer, OOP, Session/Cookie\nPROJECTS\nSocial Sphere | Full Stack Developer GitHub: github.com/lehaidangdev/social-sphere-app\n07/2025 – 02/2026\n• Project Description: A large-scale social network web application built to handle multiple user interactions and real-time features.\n• Main Functions:\n– Developed a real-time notification system with online/offline status tracking using Socket.IO.\n– Implemented robust authentication & authorization using JWT, Session, and Cookie (similar to Google auth flow).\n– Built core features including post management (like, comment, share) and group management (member approval, sorting posts).\n– Designed a user management module (profile editing, friend suggestions, relationship management) and a feed algorithm based on user preferences.\n– Optimized performance through cursor/offset pagination, server-side folder image storage to reduce database load, and data caching.\n• Technologies: TypeScript, Express.js, Sequelize ORM, SQL Server, Jest, HTML/CSS/JS, REST API, MVC.\nRetail Analytics Dashboard | Backend Developer\n12/2025 – 01/2026\ngithub.com/lehaidangdev/retail-analytics-api\nGitHub:\n• Project Description: A comprehensive dashboard system designed for monitoring sales orders, managing customers, and generating revenue statistics.\n• Main Functions: Built endpoints for real-time monitoring and near real-time analytics, dynamic revenue reporting, and detailed customer/order statistics aggregations.\n• Technologies: ASP.NET Core, SQL Server, Ocelot API Gateway, REST API."}', '{"education": {"score": 2.0, "reason": "Học viên cuối khóa tại một trường đại học hoặc cao đẳng công nghệ thông tin ở Việt Nam."}, "self_evaluation": {"score": 1.0, "reason": "Đánh giá tự đánh giá không rõ ràng và thiếu liên kết cụ thể giữa các kỹ năng và mục tiêu nghề nghiệp."}, "work_experience": {"score": 3.5, "reason": "Có ít nhất một năm làm việc trong ngành với các vị trí như Full Stack Developer và Backend Developer."}, "basic_information": {"score": 1.5, "reason": "Học sinh trung học hoặc người mới ra trường với chỉ số thời gian làm việc là 0 năm."}, "skills_specialties": {"score": 4.0, "reason": "Ứng viên có kỹ năng về TypeScript/JavaScript, C#, HTML/CSS, Jest nhưng chưa có chứng chỉ hoặc kinh nghiệm cụ thể về RESTful APIs, JWT, Redis, Docker, Kubernetes, AWS Certified Solutions Architect."}}', 'Đánh giá tổng quan cho thấy ứng viên có ít nhất một năm làm việc trong ngành với các kỹ năng cơ bản và trung bình về backend development. Tuy nhiên, ứng viên chưa có chứng chỉ hoặc kinh nghiệm cụ thể về RESTful APIs, JWT, Redis, Docker, Kubernetes, AWS Certified Solutions Architect.', 12, false, 'new', NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO public.cv_infos (id, cv_file_id, full_name, email, phone, date_of_birth, address, summary, educations, created_at, updated_at, "position", total_experience_years, raw_text, profile_data, quality_details, quality_reason, quality_score, is_marked, tag, note, work_type) VALUES (19, 21, 'PHẠM NGỌC LAN THY', 'pnthangkth@gmail.com', '0372192004', NULL, 'Hà Nội, Vietnam', 'AI Engineer with hands-on experience building LLM, RAG, and multimodal retrieval systems for education and medical use cases. Built end-to-end AI products spanning ingestion, indexing, orchestration, and evidence-grounded generation across 7 content formats, with a focus on retrieval quality, hallucination reduction, and production-ready APIs. Strong execution across Python, FastAPI, PyTorch, knowledge graphs, and agentic workflows.', '[{"field": "", "degree": "Computer Science", "university": "Posts and Telecommunications Institute of Technology (PTIT)", "graduation_year": "2026"}]', '2026-06-18 10:51:00.765326', '2026-06-18 10:51:00.765326', 'AI Engineer', 3, 'PHẠM NGỌC LAN THY
AI Engineer | LLM, RAG & Agentic Systems
Hà Nội, Vietnam | 0372192004 | pnthangkth@gmail.com | github.com/thangkh02
SUMMARY
AI Engineer with hands-on experience building LLM, RAG, and multimodal retrieval systems for education and medical use cases. Built end-to-end AI products spanning ingestion, indexing, orchestration, and evidence-grounded generation across 7 content formats, with a focus on retrieval quality, hallucination reduction, and production-ready APIs. Strong execution across Python, FastAPI, PyTorch, knowledge graphs, and agentic workflows.
EDUCATION
Posts and Telecommunications Institute of Technology (PTIT)
Computer Science
2022 – 2026
GPA: 3.23 / 4.00
PROJECTS
EduMentor Multi-Agent RAG Learning Platform
github.com/thangkh02/EduMentor
11/2025 – 12/2025
• Built an end-to-end multi-agent RAG platform that answered course questions across 7 content formats (PDF, TXT, DOC, slides, PPTX, images, video) by designing a unified ingestion, indexing, and retrieval pipeline.
• Implemented multimodal video Q&A that generated evidence-grounded answers from retrieved clips and transcripts by combining ASR, VLM-based understanding, and chunk-level retrieval.
• Developed an orchestration agent that improved response grounding by routing user intents, selecting tools, and synthesizing cited answers from retrieved context and external data sources.
• Reduced redundant recomputation for repeated queries by deploying GPTCache and retrieval-level caching for semantically similar requests.
• Shipped the platform as a web-ready backend within a 2-month development cycle using FastAPI, LangChain, PyTorch, MongoDB, and ChromaDB.
ViMed Medical Document RAG with Knowledge Graph Verification
github.com/thangkh02/VIMED-GRAPHRAG
12/2025 – 02/2026
• Built a medical GraphRAG system that improved evidence traceability by extracting knowledge triples with provenance and confidence metadata from document chunks.
• Designed a recursive tree index that enabled retrieval at multiple abstraction levels by clustering and summarizing documents into hierarchical representations.
• Engineered a hybrid retrieval pipeline that strengthened multi-hop reasoning by combining vector search with graph traversal to localize relevant subgraphs.
• Reduced unsupported responses by implementing a self-correcting verification loop that checked generated answers against citations and expanded retrieval when evidence was insufficient.
• Improved graph-based relevance modeling by training a Graph Neural Network for subgraph reranking and link prediction over the constructed knowledge graph.
• Delivered the system as a deployable API within a 3-month build cycle using FastAPI, PyTorch, ChromaDB, and Docker.
TECHNICAL SKILLS
Languages:
Python, Java, C/C++
Backend & APIs:
FastAPI, Flask, Django
ML / LLM:
PyTorch, Transformers, scikit-learn, TensorFlow/Keras, LangChain, LangGraph
RAG / AI Systems:
Vector Search, Knowledge Graph RAG, Multimodal RAG, PEFT (LoRA, QLoRA), Quantization, Distillation
Tools & Deployment:
Docker, MongoDB, ChromaDB, ONNX, llama.cpp, whisper.cpp, TFLite
CERTIFICATIONS
Samsung PTIT Applications of Algorithms (2024)
Samsung PTIT DevOps Fundamentals (2025)
