tent through natural language.\n• Focused on maximizing data security and reducing retrieval time for enterprise-level applications.\nEnd-to-End OCR & Spell Correction\nEarly 2026\nProject Contributor | GitHub | Live Demo\n• Engineered a comprehensive Optical Character Recognition (OCR) pipeline to accurately extract text from unstructured image sources based on project requirements.\n• Implemented an NLP-based spell-correction module utilizing contextual analysis, reducing Character Error Rate (CER) by over 15% from raw OCR outputs.\nDjango Backend Services\nBackend Developer | GitHub\n• Engineered a secure and scalable backend infrastructure using the Django framework, focusing on clean architecture and optimal system performance.\n• Developed robust RESTful APIs, implemented user authentication, and managed database migrations to ensure reliable and secure data workflows.\n• Designed modular backend services to support data-driven applications, ensuring code maintainability and efficiency.\nApplied Deep Learning & Computer Vision\n2023 – 2025\nSelf-Directed Study | GitHub\n• Developed and optimized object detection models including YOLOv8 for dynamic sports analytics (football/player tracking) and Faster R-CNN (ResNet50) evaluated on PASCAL VOC 2012.\n• Built foundational deep learning pipelines for image classification, managing the complete ML lifecycle from data preprocessing to model inference.\nEDUCATION\nDa Nang University of Science and Technology\n2020 – Expected Oct 2026\nDa Nang, Vietnam\nBachelor’s Degree in Information Technology\n• Relevant Coursework: Data Structures & Algorithms, Database Systems, Software Engineering, Object-Oriented Programming.\nSKILLS\n• Programming & Backend: Python, Django, Bash\n• AI & Machine Learning: PyTorch, OpenAI API, Prompt Engineering, Agentic Workflows, RAG architectures, LLaMA\n• Research Tools: Google Scholar, NotebookLM\n• Tools & Frameworks: Git, Linux, Docker\n• Languages: English (Technical Reading Proficiency), Vietnamese (Native)"}', '{"education": {"score": 1.5, "reason": "Graduated from a top-tier technical/economic university (Da Nang University of Science and Technology)."}, "self_evaluation": {"score": 0.5, "reason": "Vague, generic self-evaluation using clichéd templates (e.g., ''Results-driven AI Engineer'', ''Proven ability to own the entire ML lifecycle'')."}, "work_experience": {"score": 2, "reason": "0 - 1 years of professional experience. Worked at small-scale companies or startups (SMEs). Demonstrates baseline understanding of software development workflows."}, "basic_information": {"score": 1, "reason": "Fresher/Intern with no industry experience, track record consists only of academic or personal projects."}, "skills_specialties": {"score": 3, "reason": "Core specialized criteria for AI Engineer roles: Proficient in Python and PyTorch, with basic knowledge of SQL and foundational skills in Data Engineering. Holds recognized certifications but not listed."}}', 'The candidate is a fresher/Intern with no industry experience, holds a degree from a top-tier technical/economic university, has limited work experience at small-scale companies or startups, and demonstrates basic skills in Python and PyTorch. The self-evaluation is vague and lacks specific achievements or career roadmap.', 8, false, 'new', NULL, NULL);
